It's certainly not perfect, but I came up with it under pressure in less than 90 seconds without checking online for the modulo return values, so I'm rather proud of it.<p><?php<p>$x = 1;<p>while($x <= 100)
{<p>if((($x % 5) == 0) && (($x % 3) != 0)){ print("Buzz"); 
	}else{
	if(($x % 3) == 0){
		if(($x % 5) == 0)
		{
		 print("FizzBuzz");
		}
		else
		{
		print("Fizz");
		}
	}else{
		print($x);
	}}
	++$x;
}<p>?>
